title: Independent Abdul Khaliq Khan wins PB-51 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Abdul Khaliq Khan has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-51, Chaman by securing 20,390 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner up was Awami National Party (ANP) candidate Asghar Khan who bagged 19,623 votes.
Overall voters turn out remained 40.00 per cent.
